<HEADLINE>
28 killed as Pakistan's security forces pound militants' hideouts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, Sept. 10 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
As many as 28 people were killed as security forces pounded
militants' hideouts in Pakistan' s tribal area on Wednesday,
private DAWN NEWS TV channel reported.
</P>
<P>
The security forces pounded militants' hideouts with jets in
Bajaur Agency, leaving 28 people, including three civilians,
dead, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Backed by gunship helicopters, Pakistan Army and paramilitary
Frontier Corps on Tuesday launched a joint major and first-ever
ground operation against militants in Bajaur Agency.
</P>
<P>
They launched an operation against militants in Loisam, Rashkai
and Samkhata areas with air strikes, according to private Geo TV
channel.
</P>
<P>
Seven suspected militants were killed in the Tuesday operation,
according to Geo.
</P>
